A law that was signed in by President Zelenskyy that sets legal status and standards and creates conditions for the launch of a legal virtual assets market that will be regulated by the National Securities and Stock Market Commission.

Signed Law:
- determines the legal status, classification and ownership rights of virtual assets; 
- determines market regulators — the National Bank of Ukraine and the National Securities and Stock Market Commission; 
- creates conditions for the further formation of the legal field in the market of virtual assets;
- determines the list of virtual asset service providers and their registration conditions;
- provides for the implementation of financial monitoring measures in the field of virtual assets.

the NRA treats cryptoassets in accordance with the MAMLA definition and the European Bank Authority’s policies and identifies natural and legal persons as tax-liable parties. Other standard tax rates in Bulgaria:
